  "prompt": "What do I eat on the Ketogenics Diet?",
  "response": "On the Ketogenic Diet, you typically eat foods that are:\n\n1. High in healthy fats (70-75% of daily calories)\n\u2022 Avocados\n\u2022 Olive oil\n\u2022 Coconut oil\n\u2022 Butter\n\u2022 Fatty fish\n\u2022 Nuts and seeds\n\u2022 Full-fat dairy\n\n2. Moderate protein (20-25% of daily calories)\n\u2022 Eggs\n\u2022 Meat (beef, chicken, pork)\n\u2022 Fish and seafood\n\u2022 Some dairy products\n\n3. Low-carb vegetables\n\u2022 Spinach\n\u2022 Kale\n\u2022 Broccoli\n\u2022 Cauliflower\n\u2022 Zucchini\n\u2022 Asparagus\n\n4. Limited fruits\n\u2022 Berries (small amounts)\n\u2022 Lemons/limes\n\n5. Avoid\n\u2022 Grains\n\u2022 Sugar\n\u2022 Most fruits\n\u2022 Starchy vegetables\n\u2022 Processed foods\n\u2022 High-carb foods\n\nThe goal is to keep carbohydrate intake very low (typically 20-50 grams per day) to enter a metabolic state called ketosis, where your body burns fat for energy instead of carbohydrates.\n\nAlways consult a healthcare professional before starting any new diet.",
